    "comment": "Rationale: Analyzing parallel fiber inputs to Purkinje cells, Fig.3A shows that most vGLUT1 puncta overlapped with the punctate contactin-6 staining. Dense contactin-6 puncta were apposed to dendritic mGluR1a of Purkinje cells. These data support a presynaptic localization of contactin-6.\n\n21/6/2017 Pim\n- The rationale is:\n(1) protein expressed in axons (parallel fibers).\n(2) colocalization with pre- and postsynaptic marker proteins.\n(3) localization in synaptosomal preparations.\n- Although superresolution data is not presented, based on cell type expression and colocalization data the authors conclude: \"Col-lectively, these results indicate that NB-3 is localized presynaptically at glutamatergic synapses.\". Experimental description: \"Mice were anesthetized with pentobarbital and transcardially\nperfused\"",
